<DOC><DOCNO> AP880831-0053 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-31-88 0425EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Chile-Chronology     08-31 0460</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Chile-Chronology,0471</SECOND><HEAD>Chronology Of Main Political Events Under Pinochet Government</HEAD><HEAD>With PM-Chile, Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here is a chronology of the mainpolitical events in Chile since Gen. Augusto Pinochet seized powerin a coup 15 years ago:   Sept. 11, 1973 _ Pinochet leads the armed forces in a bloodycoup that overthrows President Salvador Allende, a Marxist electedin 1970. Allende dies in the coup and the new government says hecommitted suicide. His supporters say he was killed. A four-menMilitary Junta led by Pinochet takes power and represses supportersof the ousted leftist government. Hundreds of leftists are killedor disappear after being arrested, thousands are sent toconcentration camps or into exile. Congress is closed and politicalactivity prohibited.   June 20, 1974 _ Pinochet becomes supreme chief of the nation,retaining his post as president of the military junta.   Oct. 29, 1974 _ Exiled former army commander Gen. Carlos Pratsand his wife are killed by a bomb in Buenos Aires, Argentina, andinvolvement by Chilean secret police is suspected. The same chargearises when an exiled former foreign minister, Orlando Letelier, iskilled in a Sept 21, 1976, bombing in Washington. A U.S. courtindicts three high-ranking chilean army officers in the case, butChile refuses to extradite them.   July 9, 1977 _ Pinochet outlines a far-reaching political andinstitutional program calling for the military to remain in powerat least 11 more years.   Jan. 4, 1978 _ Pinochet, faced with growing international anddomestic comdemnation of human rights abuse, calls a nationalreferendum to seek support from the Chilean people. He wins theballot, but opposition leaders charge widespread fraud.   June. 20, 1978 _ Air force commander Gen. Gustavo Leigh, amember of the military junta, publicly challenges Pinochet'sauthority by disagreeing with the government political program.Pinochet ousts Leigh from the junta and forces him into retirement.   Sept. 11, 1980 _ Pinochet wins approval in a referendum for anew constitution that confirms his presidency until March 11, 1989.It also allows him to seek a new period of rule until 1997. Theopposition again charges massive fraud in the ballot.   March 11, 1981 _ The new constitution goes into effect.   May 11, 1983 _ Amid a deep economic crisis, the oppositionstages the first of a series of mass protests against thegovernment that left hundreds of dead and thousands arrested.   Sept. 6, 1986 _ Pinochet survives an assassination attempt by aleftist urban guerrilla commando. Five of his bodyguards werekilled and 11 wounded when the presidential motorcade is ambushedon a mountain road outside Santiago.   Aug. 30, 1988 _ The military junta nominates Pinochet as thesole candidate in an Oct. 5 presidential referendum, sparkingwidespread protests.</TEXT></DOC>